Free jabs
The free jabs — which, according to Health Director-General Patrick Amoth, are estimated at 24 million doses — expected from Gavi’s Covax Facility, will be enough to vaccinate 20 per cent of the population.
The Health Ministry has also set aside Sh10 billion to procure more doses to vaccinate an additional 10 per cent of the population during the first half of next year.
The cost of each dose ranges from Sh335 to Sh4,127 ($3 to$37); depending on the manufacturer of the vaccine. Moderna, a two-dose vaccine that received an emergency use authorisation by the United States’ Food and Drug Administration (FDA) on Friday last week, announced each dose will cost about Sh2,788 ($25), adding up to around Sh5,577 ($50) per patient.



